{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567131","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567131"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:55:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:55:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18936"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18936","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18936"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.02,0.03,0.11,0.84]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11670"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80384"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11670","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11670"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18936"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65654"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"928"},{"type":"tags","id":"937"},{"type":"tags","id":"2425"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5678"},{"type":"tags","id":"5680"},{"type":"tags","id":"5681"},{"type":"tags","id":"5770"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11282"},{"type":"tags","id":"11336"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27460"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27461"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80384","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80384"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student is studying in the hospital caf\u00e9 when they overhear another medical student discussing specific details about a patient\u0027s medical condition and treatment with classmates at a nearby table.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate immediate action for the medical student to take?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Send an email to all students about confidentiality rules","Ignore the conversation as it is between medical students","Document the breach in the patient\u0027s medical record","Inform the hospital privacy officer","Privately speak to the colleague about maintaining confidentiality"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eprivately speak to the colleague about maintaining confidentiality\u003C/strong\u003E. This approach addresses the issue directly while maintaining professional relationships and provides an opportunity for education about the importance of patient confidentiality.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInform the hospital privacy officer\u003C/strong\u003E - This escalates the situation unnecessarily before attempting to address it collegially. While appropriate in severe or recurring cases, this is not the first-line response in this situation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocument the breach in the patient\u0027s medical record\u003C/strong\u003E - This is inappropriate as the medical record should only contain clinically relevant information\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIgnore the conversation as it is between medical students\u003C/strong\u003E - This fails to address a clear breach of patient confidentiality which applies to all healthcare workers including students\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESend an email to all students about confidentiality rules\u003C/strong\u003E - This is an indirect approach that may not address the specific incident and could embarrass the colleague unnecessarily\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPatient confidentiality is a fundamental ethical and legal obligation in healthcare. All medical information should only be discussed in appropriate clinical settings with relevant healthcare team members. When breaches occur, they should be addressed promptly and professionally.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Patient confidentiality must be maintained at all times, including in public spaces and casual conversations.","Healthcare professionals have an ethical and legal obligation to address breaches of patient confidentiality when observed."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65654"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18936"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65654","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65654"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-20T15:29:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-20T15:32:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11670"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80384"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoj